{
  "question_id": "d9e7a242-4a6d-43db-86a3-ed258c137db9",
  "short_text": "Right Angled Triangle - 3 (For Loop)",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints a **Right Angled Triangle** of `N` rows using stars (`*`) and pluses (`+`).\n\nThe first `N - 1` rows contains stars (`*`) and the `Nth` row contains pluses (`+`).\n\n```\n*\n* *\n* * *\n* * * *\n+ + + + +\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every star (`*`) and every plus (`+`).\nUse **For** Loop.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows containing stars (`*`) and pluses (`+`) as a **Right Angled Triangle** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\n\n- Print stars (`*`) and pluses (`+`) on **4** rows as shown in the given image.\n  * The first **3** rows should contain stars (`*`).\n  * The **4th** row should contain `N` pluses (`+`).\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/right-angled-triangle-3.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nIn the given image, there is a space after every star (`*`) and every plus (`+`).\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n*\n* *\n* * *\n+ + + +\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "44fbc64d-f889-47fc-b953-4898323a689d",
      "code_content": "number_of_rows = int(input())\n\nfor each_number in range(1, number_of_rows + 1):\n    if each_number == number_of_rows:\n        print(\"+ \" * each_number)\n    else:\n        print(\"* \" * each_number)\n        ",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
